2) Docker : Is tool design to make it easier to create,deploy and run application by using Container.
			Docker container are lightweight alternative to VM and it uses the host OS.
			You don't have to pre allocate RAM in container.

   Ref : Docker Tutorial for Beginners - with Java and Spring Boot :
   		 Install Docker from https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/install/
   		 
   		 Step 1 : verify installation command: C:\Users\ppawar2.EAD>docker --version
									  Docker version 19.03.8, build afacb8b

		 Step 2 : here we have different image of docker : https://hub.docker.com/u/in28min
		 
		 Step 3: Command to run the image from hub in local.
		 		 docker run in28min/todo-rest-api-h2:1.0.0.RELEASE
		 		 
